II Armored Division soldier in Europe","body":"Clarence Irving 'Cookie' Cook was born February 1, 1918 in Medina NY — barely a month before the U.S. War Department was authorizing the operations that would lead to his Uncle Jay Hebner's death in France that September. Twenty-five years later, Clarence would follow his uncle into European combat. He served in the U.S. Army's Armored Division in the European Theater during World War II."}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"clarence-cook-1918"},"X02272":{"id":"X02272","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false},"bio":{"first_name":"Catherine","middle_name":"Evelyn","last_name":"Cook","maiden_name":"Lindke","married_names":["Gilbert","Cook"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Catherine Evelyn Lindke Gilbert Cook"},"birth":{"year":1921,"country":"United States"},"death":{"year":2001,"country":"United States"},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"HD3256","location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1977,"children_ids":[]}],"tags":[],"sources":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"catherine-lindke-1921"},"HD3257":{"id":"HD3257","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":12},"bio":{"first_name":"Donald","middle_name":"David","last_name":"Cook","married_names":[],"nickname":"Cookie","gender":"male","display_name":"Donald David \"Cookie\" Cook","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777239953/doncookie_cvz0n2.jpg","photo_notes":"Cloudinary-hosted; supplied by Sam"},"birth":{"year":1922,"month":1,"day":23,"city":"Medina","county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":2004,"month":11,"day":20,"city":"Medina","county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM150","plot_notes":"Boxwood Cemetery, Medina Orleans County NY"},"parents":{"father_id":"X02271","mother_id":"HD3255"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02273","date_year":1955,"location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1967,"children_ids":[]}],"tags":["wwii"],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave (Donald David Cook memorial, Boxwood Cemetery Medina)"},{"short":"Tom Rivers (Editor), 'Gravestone coming for Medina man killed in World War I,' Orleans Hub, May 28, 2016 — references Don Cook as Debbie Morse's father, prominent local photographer, WWII veteran, d.2004"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"profession","header":"Prominent Medina photographer and WWII veteran","body":"Donald David 'Cookie' Cook was born January 23, 1922 in Medina NY, four years after his uncle Jay Hebner was killed in France. Don served in World War II and returned to become a prominent local photographer in Orleans County — the visual chronicler of mid-20th-century Medina life. He died November 20, 2004 in his hometown at age 82, buried at Boxwood Cemetery near his parents and his great-grandparents the Hebners."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"His daughter Debbie restored Jay's memory","body":"Don's daughter Dabrina D. 'Debbie' Cook Morse — Don's youngest of four — was the person who in 2016 finally brought a memorial to Medina for her great-uncle Jay Hebner. Don had told Debbie about the uncle killed in WWI; after Don's 2004 death, Debbie and her husband Jim researched Jay's records, located his Saint-Mihiel American Cemetery grave in France, and paid out of pocket for a cenotaph at Boxwood Cemetery near the family Hebner and Cook plots. As Debbie said in May 2016: 'It's about bringing honor to him."}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"donald-cook-1922"},"X02273":{"id":"X02273","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false},"bio":{"first_name":"Shirley","middle_name":"Marie","last_name":"Cook","maiden_name":"Perry","married_names":["Cook"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Shirley Marie Perry Cook"},"birth":{"year":1936,"month":8,"day":6,"city":"Wethersfield Springs","county":"Wyoming County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1967,"month":10,"day":2,"city":"Medina","county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD3257","date_year":1955,"location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1967,"children_ids":[]}],"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave (Shirley Marie Perry Cook memorial)"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[],"cross_connections":[],"resid